cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with machine learning and proposes a new loss function to address the problem of nonconforming residual distributions. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper discusses the use of the wrapped loss function for backpropagation optimization, which is a common technique in these sub-categories.
